===Etymology===
[[File:Icelandic horse1.jpg|thumb|right|250px]]
{{liushu|p}}; derived from the pictogram of a horse with its head turned to look back and showing a flowing mane in the wind. The four short strokes at its base ([[灬]]) represent its feet, and the sweeping hook stroke in the lower right represents its tail.

Compare also {{term|鳥||bird|sc=Hani}}, whose current form is similar (graphically, [[灬]] for claws/legs).

Contrast with {{term|鹿||deer|sc=Hani}}, which saw a very different development, and {{term|𢊁||bison|sc=Hani}} (as in [[薦]]), which is a hybrid: it has the the legs of 馬 (灬) but the head of 鹿.

